    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Pringle</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16,
                                    1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 79.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I append a copy of your telegram of 8th
                            instant, reporting the statement of Mr. Peterson, consul at Tegucigalpa,
                            that if any Americans in the army of Vasquez should be captured by
                            Bonilla they will be shot.</p>
                <p>In an interview with the minister of Nicaragua, I find that Dr. Guzmán
                            does not share Mr. Peterson’s apprehensions.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
